This paper discusses the implementation of batch backpropagation algorithms in neural networks, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of stochastic gradient descent and optimization in many dimensions also suggests a focus on neural networks and optimization (cs.NE). Additionally, the mention of tasks conventionally considered only doable by humans implies a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of tensor operations suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
